latestPosts.caption:
Banarasi sarees have roots in the city of ghats - Banaras/Varanasi, but they are widely worn throughout the country. West Bengal and Kolkata are two places where one can find women embracing these timeless beauties the most. Banarasi sarees have found a special and nearly permanent place in the hearts of Bengali women.
Their special characteristics include intricate intertwining floral and foliate motifs, kalga and bel, a string of upright leaves called jhallar at the outer, edge of border is a characteristic of these saris.

This is the Ministry Of Cultures tribute on behalf of the nation to the women power of India and the millions of weavers of India who have kept this timeless tradition alive through ages, passing the skill through generations.

 
This year @amritmahotsav has arranged a contest where you can get a chance to featured on their official page. If you want to get that spotlight, you need to post a picture of yourself in a traditional saree using the hash tag #bharatkinariinsari and you have to tag three of your female friends to participate in this contest. 

@amritmahotsav
@ministryofculturegoi

Honoured to be a part of this campaign.
#republicdayindia
